==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gama grass
<hw>Ga"ma grass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From <ets>Gama</ets>, a
cluster of the Maldive Islands.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species
of grass (<spn>Tripsacum dactyloides</spn>) tall, stout, and exceedingly
productive; cultivated in the West Indies, Mexico, and the Southern
States of North America as a forage grass; -- called also
<altname>sesame grass</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

